Learning Objective
Introduction 
Database foundation refers to the fundamental infrastructure and underlying technology that supports data storage, retrieval, and management. It encompasses various database systems and architectures, ensuring data integrity, scalability, and efficient access
Focus: Introduction to Database & DBMS, Relational Database Overview, Working with MariaDB, Schema design, Database Transactions & ER diagrams
Prerequisites: NA
Theme
Google is one of the largest consumers of databases worldwide, given the scale of its operations. They have developed and used various database systems, including Google Cloud Spanner, Bigtable, and Firestore, to support their search engine, advertising platforms, and other services. Google Cloud Spanner is particularly known for providing a globally distributed, horizontally scalable, and strongly consistent database foundation.
Amazon is another tech giant that relies heavily on databases to power its e-commerce platform, AWS services, and various other products. Amazon Aurora, a fully managed relational database service, is one of the key Database Foundation solutions they offer to customers. Aurora provides high performance, scalability, and reliability, making it ideal for their business needs.
Primary Goals
Develop a solid understanding of what databases are, their importance in modern computing, and their role in data management.
Learn about Database Management Systems (DBMS) and their significance in managing and organizing data efficiently.
Gain a comprehensive understanding of relational databases, including their components, structure, and how data is organized using tables.
Master the art of designing efficient database schemas. Learn how to create well-structured tables, define relationships between them, and optimize data storage.
Learn how to create and interpret ER diagrams, which are essential tools for designing databases. Understand how to model entities, attributes, and relationships between entities.
Understand the principles of database normalization, which involves minimizing data redundancy and ensuring data integrity through the elimination of certain types of anomalies.
Chapter Essentials
Learning Lessons
The chapter comprises multiple lessons centered around Database fundamentals, Relational Database, Database Transactions, and ER diagram.
The lesson consists of learning material and engaging activities that enhance the learner's experience.
In addition, every lesson includes 10 MCQs aimed at enhancing knowledge.
Skill Mastery Challenge
The chapter includes a Skill Mastery Challenge with a Summary section for the given chapter for best practices, challenges, and additional references, an Interview Prep section with industry-specific concepts, and a Competency Challenge featuring a one-hour session with 40 MCQs for reinforced learning and identifying improvement areas.
Earning the Competency Challenge Certificate will ensure the completion of this chapter.
